juniL2tpMIB.name: juniL2tpMIB

revisions.description: juniL2tpSessionStatusProxyLcp will present session status for both LAC and LNS. Added juniL2tpSysConfigDestinationLockoutTimeout, juniL2tpSysConfigDestinationLockoutTestEnabled, juniL2tpDestConfigLockoutAction.

Added juniL2tpSysStatusTotalSwitchedSessions, juniL2tpSysStatusFailedSwitchedSessions, juniL2tpSysStatusActiveSwitchedSessions, juniL2tpSysStatusIfCounterDiscontinuityTime, juniL2tpSysConfigRejectTxAddressChange and juniL2tpSysConfigShortDrainTimeout. Added values to juniL2tpSysConfigIgnoreTxAddressChange.
Added juniL2tpSysConfigIgnoreTxAddressChange. Added juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteReceiveAddress and juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteReceivePort.

Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names. Added new objects juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissionsEstablished, juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissionsNotEstablished, juniL2tpSysConfigDisableChallenge, Deprecated juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissions.
Added new objects juniL2tpSysConfigTunnelSwitchingEnabled, juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissions, juniL2tpSysConfigTunnelIdleTimeout.

Added juniL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex as long-term replacement for juniL2tpSessionStatusLacPppIfIndex. Added new objects juniL2tpTunnelStatusCumEstabTime, juniL2tpSessionStatusCumEstabTime, juniL2tpSessionStatPayLostPackets. Changed range of juniL2tpSysConfigDestructTimeout to 10-3600.
Initial revision, based in part on IETF L2TP Working Group draft-ietf-l2tpext-l2tp-mib-01.

juniL2tpMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniL2tpMIB.description: The L2TP MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise.

JuniL2tpTunnelId.name: JuniL2tpTunnelId
JuniL2tpTunnelId.description: An L2TP Tunnel ID. Implementation constraints may restrict the range of values actually used.

JuniL2tpSessionId.name: JuniL2tpSessionId
JuniL2tpSessionId.description: An L2TP Session ID. Implementation constraints may restrict the range of values actually used.

JuniL2tpAdminState.name: JuniL2tpAdminState
JuniL2tpAdminState.description: The administrative state exerted on L2TP tunnels sessions at some scope of control. enabled New tunnels/sessions may be instantiated. disabled All tunnels/sessions are terminated. drain No new tunnels/sessions may be instantiated, but any existing tunnels/sessions may persist until they expire by other means. The DESCRIPTION clause of an object defined to have this syntax must describe the scope of control that object exerts (e.g., all tunnels/sessions across the system, sessions within a single tunnel, etc.).

JuniL2tpTransport.name: JuniL2tpTransport
JuniL2tpTransport.description: Transport type over which L2TP is carried.

JuniL2tpLockoutAction.name: JuniL2tpLockoutAction
JuniL2tpLockoutAction.description: The lockout action applied to an L2TP destinations. none No action test Test and unlock if successful unlock Unconditional unlock

JuniL2tpLockoutState.name: JuniL2tpLockoutState
JuniL2tpLockoutState.description: The lockout state of an L2TP destination. notLocked not locked waitLockTimeout waiting for lockout timeout expiration waitTestStart waiting for lockout test start testing lockout test active

juniL2tpSysConfigAdminState.name: juniL2tpSysConfigAdminState
juniL2tpSysConfigAdminState.description: Exerts control over all L2TP tunnels/sessions in the system.

juniL2tpSysConfigDestructTimeout.name: juniL2tpSysConfigDestructTimeout
juniL2tpSysConfigDestructTimeout.description: The amount of time, in seconds, to preserve dynamic tunnels/sessions after they become inactive, e.g. to poll their statistics.

juniL2tpSysConfigIpChecksumEnable.name: juniL2tpSysConfigIpChecksumEnable
juniL2tpSysConfigIpChecksumEnable.description: Enable/disable IP checksumming for tunnels with UDP/IP transport.

juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissions.name: juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissions
juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissions.description: The number of retransmission retries allowed before control connection goes down. This object has been replaced by juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissionsEstablished and juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissionsNotEstablished.

juniL2tpSysConfigTunnelIdleTimeout.name: juniL2tpSysConfigTunnelIdleTimeout
juniL2tpSysConfigTunnelIdleTimeout.description: Idle tunnel remains active for the specified amount of time; value 0 disables the timer i.e. tunnel becomes persistent.

juniL2tpSysConfigReceiveDataSequencingIg.name: juniL2tpSysConfigReceiveDataSequencingIgnore
juniL2tpSysConfigReceiveDataSequencingIg.description: Enable/disable ignoring of receive sequencing of L2TP data packets.

juniL2tpSysConfigFailoverWithinPreferenc.name: juniL2tpSysConfigFailoverWithinPreference
juniL2tpSysConfigFailoverWithinPreferenc.description: Enable/disable fail-over within a preference level.

juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissionsE.name: juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissionsEstablished
juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissionsE.description: It represents number of retries allowed for established tunnels before control connection goes down.

juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissionsN.name: juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissionsNotEstablished
juniL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissionsN.description: It represents number of retries allowed for unestablished tunnels before control connection goes down.

juniL2tpSysConfigDisableChallenge.name: juniL2tpSysConfigDisableChallenge
juniL2tpSysConfigDisableChallenge.description: Disable inclusion of chap challenge in the outgoing packets.

juniL2tpSysConfigDisableCallingNumberAvp.name: juniL2tpSysConfigDisableCallingNumberAvp
juniL2tpSysConfigDisableCallingNumberAvp.description: Enable/disable inclusion of calling number avp in ICRQ packet.

juniL2tpSysConfigIgnoreTxAddressChange.name: juniL2tpSysConfigIgnoreTxAddressChange
juniL2tpSysConfigIgnoreTxAddressChange.description: Configure L2TP to ignore IP address and/or UDP port changes on incoming SCCRP messages. When this feature is enabled the L2TP tunnel may have separate receive and transmit address and/or port values to the remote host. disable(0) - change is not ignored ipAddressAndUdpPort(1)- ignore both address and port changes ipAddress(2) - ignore address changes only udpPort(3) - ignore port changes only.

juniL2tpSysConfigEnableDisconnectCauseAv.name: juniL2tpSysConfigEnableDisconnectCauseAvp
juniL2tpSysConfigEnableDisconnectCauseAv.description: Enable/disable inclusion of L2TP PPP Disconnect Cause AVP in CDN packet.

juniL2tpSysConfigReceiveWindowSize.name: juniL2tpSysConfigReceiveWindowSize
juniL2tpSysConfigReceiveWindowSize.description: Configure the global L2TP receive window size. A value of 0 indicates the system chooses the RWS. This object may be overwritten by other more specific RWS settings.

juniL2tpSysConfigEnableRxSpeedAvpWhenEqu.name: juniL2tpSysConfigEnableRxSpeedAvpWhenEqual
juniL2tpSysConfigEnableRxSpeedAvpWhenEqu.description: Enable/disable generation of L2TP RX speed AVP when RX and TX speeds are equal. Note the RX speed is always generated when the RX and TX speeds differ.

juniL2tpSysConfigRejectTxAddressChange.name: juniL2tpSysConfigRejectTxAddressChange
juniL2tpSysConfigRejectTxAddressChange.description: Configure L2TP to reject IP address and/or UDP port changes on incomming SCCRP messages. disable(0) - address change is allowed ipAddressAndUdpPort(1)- reject both address and port changes ipAddress(2) - reject address changes only udpPort(3) - reject port changes only.

juniL2tpSysConfigShortDrainTimeout.name: juniL2tpSysConfigShortDrainTimeout
juniL2tpSysConfigShortDrainTimeout.description: Configure the L2TP short drain interval. This interval represents the time a tunnel, that is already draining, will continue to drain upon receiving a start request.

juniL2tpSysConfigDestinationLockoutTestE.name: juniL2tpSysConfigDestinationLockoutTestEnabled
juniL2tpSysConfigDestinationLockoutTestE.description: Enable/disable testing of failed destiantion before removing lockout.

juniL2tpSysConfigDestinationLockoutTimeo.name: juniL2tpSysConfigDestinationLockoutTimeout
juniL2tpSysConfigDestinationLockoutTimeo.description: Failed destination remains locked out for the specified amount of time.

juniL2tpSysConfigFailoverResync.name: juniL2tpSysConfigFailoverResync
juniL2tpSysConfigFailoverResync.description: Configure L2TP failover resync mechanism. disable(0) - Disable failover resync failoverProtocol(1) - Use the L2TP Failover Protocol silentFailover(2) - Use the JUNOSe Silent Failover Mechanism failoverProtocolFallbackToSilentFailover(3) - (Default) Use the L2TP Failover Protocol and fall back to Silent Failover.

juniL2tpSysStatusProtocolVersion.name: juniL2tpSysStatusProtocolVersion
juniL2tpSysStatusProtocolVersion.description: Vector of supported L2TP protocol version and revision numbers. Supported versions are identified via a two octet pairing where the first octet indicates the version and the second octet contains the revision.

juniL2tpSysStatusVendorName.name: juniL2tpSysStatusVendorName
juniL2tpSysStatusVendorName.description: Vendor name of the L2TP protocol stack.

juniL2tpSysStatusFirmwareRev.name: juniL2tpSysStatusFirmwareRev
juniL2tpSysStatusFirmwareRev.description: Firmware revision for the L2TP protocol stack.

juniL2tpSysStatusFailedDestinations.name: juniL2tpSysStatusFailedDestinations
juniL2tpSysStatusFailedDestinations.description: Number of destination creation attempts that failed.

juniL2tpSysStatusActiveDestinations.name: juniL2tpSysStatusActiveDestinations
juniL2tpSysStatusActiveDestinations.description: Number of destinations having at least one active tunnel.

juniL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnels.name: juniL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnels
juniL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnels.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

juniL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.name: juniL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnelAuthens
juniL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed authentication.

juniL2tpSysStatusFailedSessions.name: juniL2tpSysStatusFailedSessions
juniL2tpSysStatusFailedSessions.description: Number of session creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

juniL2tpSysStatusTotalSwitchedSessions.name: juniL2tpSysStatusTotalSwitchedSessions
juniL2tpSysStatusTotalSwitchedSessions.description: Number of switched session creations attempted.

juniL2tpSysStatusFailedSwitchedSessions.name: juniL2tpSysStatusFailedSwitchedSessions
juniL2tpSysStatusFailedSwitchedSessions.description: Number of switched session creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

juniL2tpSysStatusActiveSwitchedSessions.name: juniL2tpSysStatusActiveSwitchedSessions
juniL2tpSysStatusActiveSwitchedSessions.description: Number of switched sessions currently established.

juniL2tpSysStatusIfCounterDiscontinuityT.name: juniL2tpSysStatusIfCounterDiscontinuityTime
juniL2tpSysStatusIfCounterDiscontinuityT.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which any one or more of the system-level status and statistics suffered a discontinuity. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re- initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

juniL2tpDestConfigTable.name: juniL2tpDestConfigTable
juniL2tpDestConfigTable.description: The L2TP destination configuration table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in juniL2tpDestStatsTable.

juniL2tpDestConfigEntry.name: juniL2tpDestConfigEntry
juniL2tpDestConfigEntry.description: Describes the configuration attributes of an L2TP destination.

juniL2tpDestConfigIfIndex.name: juniL2tpDestConfigIfIndex
juniL2tpDestConfigIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

juniL2tpDestConfigRowStatus.name: juniL2tpDestConfigRowStatus
juniL2tpDestConfigRowStatus.description: An implementation may choose not to support administrative configuration of tunnels.

juniL2tpDestConfigLockoutAction.name: juniL2tpDestConfigLockoutAction
juniL2tpDestConfigLockoutAction.description: The lockout action to be applied to a destination.

juniL2tpDestStatusTable.name: juniL2tpDestStatusTable
juniL2tpDestStatusTable.description: The L2TP destination status table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in juniL2tpDestConfigTable.

juniL2tpDestStatusEntry.name: juniL2tpDestStatusEntry
juniL2tpDestStatusEntry.description: Describes the status attributes of an L2TP destination.

juniL2tpDestStatusIfIndex.name: juniL2tpDestStatusIfIndex
juniL2tpDestStatusIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

juniL2tpDestStatusTransport.name: juniL2tpDestStatusTransport
juniL2tpDestStatusTransport.description: The underlying transport over which this L2TP destination is carried.

juniL2tpDestStatusEffectiveAdminState.name: juniL2tpDestStatusEffectiveAdminState
juniL2tpDestStatusEffectiveAdminState.description: The administrative state currently in effect. This could be the configured admin state for this destination, or an overriding admin state exerted from a higher hierarchical level (system).

juniL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnels.name: juniL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnels
juniL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnels.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

juniL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.name: juniL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnelAuthens
juniL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed authentication.

juniL2tpDestStatusFailedSessions.name: juniL2tpDestStatusFailedSessions
juniL2tpDestStatusFailedSessions.description: Number of session creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

juniL2tpDestStatTable.name: juniL2tpDestStatTable
juniL2tpDestStatTable.description: The L2TP destination statistics table. Describes the aggregate control and payload statistics for all L2TP tunnels configured on each destination. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in juniL2tpDestConfigTable.

juniL2tpDestStatEntry.name: juniL2tpDestStatEntry
juniL2tpDestStatEntry.description: Describes the aggregate L2TP control and payload statistics for all L2TP tunnels on an L2TP destination.

juniL2tpDestStatIfIndex.name: juniL2tpDestStatIfIndex
juniL2tpDestStatIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

juniL2tpDestStatCtlRecvErrors.name: juniL2tpDestStatCtlRecvErrors
juniL2tpDestStatCtlRecvErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring reception errors.

juniL2tpDestStatCtlRecvDiscards.name: juniL2tpDestStatCtlRecvDiscards
juniL2tpDestStatCtlRecvDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded after reception.

juniL2tpDestStatCtlSendErrors.name: juniL2tpDestStatCtlSendErrors
juniL2tpDestStatCtlSendErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring transmission errors.

juniL2tpDestStatCtlSendDiscards.name: juniL2tpDestStatCtlSendDiscards
juniL2tpDestStatCtlSendDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded before transmission.

juniL2tpDestStatPayRecvErrors.name: juniL2tpDestStatPayRecvErrors
juniL2tpDestStatPayRecvErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring reception errors.

juniL2tpDestStatPayRecvDiscards.name: juniL2tpDestStatPayRecvDiscards
juniL2tpDestStatPayRecvDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded after reception.

juniL2tpDestStatPaySendErrors.name: juniL2tpDestStatPaySendErrors
juniL2tpDestStatPaySendErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring transmission errors.

juniL2tpDestStatPaySendDiscards.name: juniL2tpDestStatPaySendDiscards
juniL2tpDestStatPaySendDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded before transmission.

juniL2tpTunnelConfigTable.name: juniL2tpTunnelConfigTable
juniL2tpTunnelConfigTable.description: The L2TP tunnel configuration table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in juniL2tpTunnelStatsTable.

juniL2tpTunnelConfigEntry.name: juniL2tpTunnelConfigEntry
juniL2tpTunnelConfigEntry.description: Describes the configuration attributes of an L2TP tunnel.

juniL2tpTunnelConfigIfIndex.name: juniL2tpTunnelConfigIfIndex
juniL2tpTunnelConfigIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

juniL2tpTunnelConfigRowStatus.name: juniL2tpTunnelConfigRowStatus
juniL2tpTunnelConfigRowStatus.description: An implementation may choose not to support administrative configuration of tunnels.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusTable.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusTable
juniL2tpTunnelStatusTable.description: The L2TP tunnel status and statistics table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in juniL2tpTunnelConfigTable.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusEntry.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusEntry
juniL2tpTunnelStatusEntry.description: An L2TP tunnel interface stats entry.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusIfIndex.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusIfIndex
juniL2tpTunnelStatusIfIndex.description: Same as the value of ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusTransport.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusTransport
juniL2tpTunnelStatusTransport.description: The underlying transport over which this L2TP tunnel is carried.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusEffectiveAdminState.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusEffectiveAdminState
juniL2tpTunnelStatusEffectiveAdminState.description: The administrative state currently in effect. This could be the configured admin state for this tunnel, or an overriding admin state exerted from a higher hierarchical level (system, destination).

juniL2tpTunnelStatusState.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusState
juniL2tpTunnelStatusState.description: The current state of the tunnel.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusInitiated.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusInitiated
juniL2tpTunnelStatusInitiated.description: Indicates whether the tunnel was initiated locally, or by the remote tunnel peer.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteHostName.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteHostName
juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteHostName.description: The host name obtained during the tunnel establishment phase (via the Host Name AVP) of the L2TP peer. If the tunnel is idle, this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, or a zero-length string if no name was previously known.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteVendorName.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteVendorName
juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteVendorName.description: Identifies the vendor name of the peer's L2TP implementation. If the tunnel is idle, this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, of a zero-length string if no name was previously known.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFirmwareRevisi.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFirmwareRevision
juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFirmwareRevisi.description: The tunnel peer's firmware revision number. If the tunnel is idle, this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, or a zero value if no revision was previously known.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteProtocolVersio.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteProtocolVersion
juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteProtocolVersio.description: The protocol version and revision of the tunnel peer's implementation. The first octet contains the protocol version. The second octet contains the protocol revision.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteBearerCapabili.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteBearerCapabilities
juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteBearerCapabili.description: The Bearer Capabilities of the tunnel peer. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, or 'none' if not previously known.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFramingCapabil.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFramingCapabilities
juniL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFramingCapabil.description: The Framing Capabilities of the tunnel peer. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, or 'none' if not previously known.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendWindowSize.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendWindowSize
juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendWindowSize.description: The tunnel peer's receive window size.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendQueueDepth.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendQueueDepth
juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendQueueDepth.description: Number of control packets on transmit queue.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeq.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeq
juniL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeq.description: The next sequence number expected in a received control packet.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeqAck.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeqAck
juniL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeqAck.description: The last received sequence number that was acknowledged back to the tunnel peer.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeq.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeq
juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeq.description: The next sequence number to be sent in a transmitted control packet.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeqAck.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeqAck
juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeqAck.description: The send sequence number that the tunnel peer has acknowledged. The flow control state can be determined by subtracting the juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeq from juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeqAck and comparing this value to juniL2tpTunnelStatusSendWindowSize.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusTotalSessions.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusTotalSessions
juniL2tpTunnelStatusTotalSessions.description: The total number of sessions that this tunnel has successfully connected through to its tunnel peer since this tunnel was created, including those that have since terminated.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusFailedSessions.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusFailedSessions
juniL2tpTunnelStatusFailedSessions.description: The number of sessions that were initiated but failed to reach the established phase.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusActiveSessions.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusActiveSessions
juniL2tpTunnelStatusActiveSessions.description: The current number of sessions in the established state.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusLastResultCode.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusLastResultCode
juniL2tpTunnelStatusLastResultCode.description: The last value of the result code as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorCode.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorCode
juniL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorCode.description: The last value of the error code as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorMessage.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorMessage
juniL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorMessage.description: The last value of the optional message as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

juniL2tpTunnelStatusCumEstabTime.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusCumEstabTime
juniL2tpTunnelStatusCumEstabTime.description: The cumulative time in seconds that this tunnel, since first being created, has spent in the established state (which may be punctuated by intervals outside the established state).

juniL2tpTunnelStatusEffectiveFailoverRes.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatusEffectiveFailoverResync
juniL2tpTunnelStatusEffectiveFailoverRes.description: The mechanism employed following failover to resynchronize with the L2TP peer.

juniL2tpTunnelStatTable.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatTable
juniL2tpTunnelStatTable.description: The L2TP tunnel statistics table. Describes the control and payload statistics for each L2TP tunnel. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in juniL2tpTunnelConfigTable.

juniL2tpTunnelStatEntry.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatEntry
juniL2tpTunnelStatEntry.description: Describes the L2TP control and payload statistics for an L2TP tunnel.

juniL2tpTunnelStatIfIndex.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatIfIndex
juniL2tpTunnelStatIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvErrors.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvErrors
juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring reception errors.

juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvDiscards.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvDiscards
juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded after reception.

juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendErrors.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendErrors
juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring transmission errors.

juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendDiscards.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendDiscards
juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded before transmission.

juniL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvErrors.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvErrors
juniL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring reception errors.

juniL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvDiscards.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvDiscards
juniL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded after reception.

juniL2tpTunnelStatPaySendErrors.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatPaySendErrors
juniL2tpTunnelStatPaySendErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring transmission errors.

juniL2tpTunnelStatPaySendDiscards.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatPaySendDiscards
juniL2tpTunnelStatPaySendDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded before transmission.

juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvZLB.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvZLB
juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvZLB.description: Number of Zero Length Body control packet acknowledgement packets that were received.

juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfSequence.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfSequence
juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfSequence.description: Number of control packets not received in the correct sequence number order.

juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfWindow.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfWindow
juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfWindow.description: Number of control packets received outside the offered receive window.

juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendZLB.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendZLB
juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendZLB.description: Number of Zero Length Body control packets sent.

juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendRetransmits.name: juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendRetransmits
juniL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendRetransmits.description: Number of control packet send retransmissions.

juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifEntry.name: juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifEntry
juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifEntry.description: A mapping of TunnelIf/SessionId to SessionIf.

juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifTunnelIfIndex.name: juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifTunnelIfIndex
juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifTunnelIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of a tunnel interface.

juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifLocalSessionId.name: juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifLocalSessionId
juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifLocalSessionId.description: A local session ID on the associated tunnel interface.

juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifSessionIfIndex.name: juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifSessionIfIndex
juniL2tpMapTifSidToSifSessionIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the session interface identified by this entry's Tunnel ifIndex and local Session ID pair.

juniL2tpMapTidToTifTable.name: juniL2tpMapTidToTifTable
juniL2tpMapTidToTifTable.description: Map L2TP tunnel IDs to tunnel interfaces.

juniL2tpMapTidToTifEntry.name: juniL2tpMapTidToTifEntry
juniL2tpMapTidToTifEntry.description: A mapping of L2TP tunnel ID to tunnel interface.

juniL2tpMapTidToTifIfIndex.name: juniL2tpMapTidToTifIfIndex
juniL2tpMapTidToTifIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the tunnel interface having the associated tunnel identifier.

juniL2tpSessionConfigTable.name: juniL2tpSessionConfigTable
juniL2tpSessionConfigTable.description: The L2TP session configuration table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in juniL2tpSessionStatsTable.

juniL2tpSessionConfigEntry.name: juniL2tpSessionConfigEntry
juniL2tpSessionConfigEntry.description: Describes the configuration attributes of an L2TP session.

juniL2tpSessionConfigIfIndex.name: juniL2tpSessionConfigIfIndex
juniL2tpSessionConfigIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

juniL2tpSessionConfigRowStatus.name: juniL2tpSessionConfigRowStatus
juniL2tpSessionConfigRowStatus.description: An implementation may choose not to support administrative configuration of tunnels.

juniL2tpSessionStatusTable.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusTable
juniL2tpSessionStatusTable.description: The L2TP session status and statistics table.

juniL2tpSessionStatusEntry.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusEntry
juniL2tpSessionStatusEntry.description: An L2TP session interface status and statistics entry.

juniL2tpSessionStatusIfIndex.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusIfIndex
juniL2tpSessionStatusIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an L2TP session interface.

juniL2tpSessionStatusLacPppIfIndex.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusLacPppIfIndex
juniL2tpSessionStatusLacPppIfIndex.description: For pass-through PPP sessions (conventional LAC), the ifIndex of an associated local PPP interface through which the remote LAC client was connected. If unknown, this object contains a value of zero. For locally originated PPP sessions (LNS-like), this object has a value of zero. This object is deprecated in favor of juniL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex.

juniL2tpSessionStatusLocalSessionId.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusLocalSessionId
juniL2tpSessionStatusLocalSessionId.description: The local session ID for the session.

juniL2tpSessionStatusRemoteSessionId.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusRemoteSessionId
juniL2tpSessionStatusRemoteSessionId.description: The remote session ID for the session.

juniL2tpSessionStatusUserName.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusUserName
juniL2tpSessionStatusUserName.description: The peer session name on this interface, typically the login name of the remote user. If the user name is unknown this object will contain a zero-length string.

juniL2tpSessionStatusEffectiveAdminState.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusEffectiveAdminState
juniL2tpSessionStatusEffectiveAdminState.description: The administrative state currently in effect. This could be the configured admin state for this session, or an overriding admin state exerted from a higher hierarchical level (system, destination, tunnel).

juniL2tpSessionStatusState.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusState
juniL2tpSessionStatusState.description: The current state of the session.

juniL2tpSessionStatusCallType.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusCallType
juniL2tpSessionStatusCallType.description: The type of call and role this tunnel peer is providing for this session. For example, lacIncoming(1) indicates this tunnel peer is acting as a LAC and generated a Incoming-Call-Request to the tunnel peer (the LNS). Note that tunnel peers can be both LAC and LNS simultaneously.

juniL2tpSessionStatusCallSerialNumber.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusCallSerialNumber
juniL2tpSessionStatusCallSerialNumber.description: The serial number assigned to this session.

juniL2tpSessionStatusTxConnectSpeed.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusTxConnectSpeed
juniL2tpSessionStatusTxConnectSpeed.description: The last known transmit baud rate for this session.

juniL2tpSessionStatusRxConnectSpeed.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusRxConnectSpeed
juniL2tpSessionStatusRxConnectSpeed.description: The last known receive baud rate for this session.

juniL2tpSessionStatusCallBearerType.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusCallBearerType
juniL2tpSessionStatusCallBearerType.description: The bearer type of this session.

juniL2tpSessionStatusFramingType.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusFramingType
juniL2tpSessionStatusFramingType.description: The framing type of this session.

juniL2tpSessionStatusPhysChanId.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusPhysChanId
juniL2tpSessionStatusPhysChanId.description: The physical channel identifier for the session. For pass-through PPP sessions, typically the ifIndex of the access interface lying below the PPP interface identified by juniL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex.

juniL2tpSessionStatusDnis.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusDnis
juniL2tpSessionStatusDnis.description: The Dialed Number Information String that the LAC obtained from the network for the session. If no DNIS was provided, a zero-length string will be returned.

juniL2tpSessionStatusClid.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusClid
juniL2tpSessionStatusClid.description: The Calling Line ID that the LAC obtained from the network for the session. If no CLID was provided, a zero-length string will be returned.

juniL2tpSessionStatusSubAddress.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusSubAddress
juniL2tpSessionStatusSubAddress.description: The SubAddress that the LAC obtained from the network for the session. If no SubAddress was provided, a zero-length string will be returned.

juniL2tpSessionStatusPrivateGroupId.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusPrivateGroupId
juniL2tpSessionStatusPrivateGroupId.description: The Private Group Identifier used for this tunneled session. If no Private Group Identifier was provided, a zero-length string will be returned.

juniL2tpSessionStatusProxyLcp.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusProxyLcp
juniL2tpSessionStatusProxyLcp.description: Indicates whether proxy LCP was provided for this session.

juniL2tpSessionStatusAuthMethod.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusAuthMethod
juniL2tpSessionStatusAuthMethod.description: The proxy authentication method employed by the LAC for the session. If juniL2tpSessionProxyLcp is false(2) this object reports a value of 'none' and should be ignored.

juniL2tpSessionStatusSequencingState.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusSequencingState
juniL2tpSessionStatusSequencingState.description: Indicates which tunnel peers have requested payload sequencing.

juniL2tpSessionStatusRecvSeq.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusRecvSeq
juniL2tpSessionStatusRecvSeq.description: The next receive sequence number expected.

juniL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex
juniL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex.description: For pass-through remote client sessions (conventional LAC), the ifIndex of an associated local interface through which the remote LAC client was connected. If unknown, this object contains a value of zero. For locally originated sessions (LNS-like), this object has a value of zero.

juniL2tpSessionStatusCumEstabTime.name: juniL2tpSessionStatusCumEstabTime
juniL2tpSessionStatusCumEstabTime.description: The cumulative time in seconds that this session, since first being created, has spent in the established state (which may be punctuated by intervals outside the established state).

juniL2tpSessionStatEntry.name: juniL2tpSessionStatEntry
juniL2tpSessionStatEntry.description: An L2TP session interface statistics entry.

juniL2tpSessionStatIfIndex.name: juniL2tpSessionStatIfIndex
juniL2tpSessionStatIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an L2TP session interface.

juniL2tpSessionStatPayRecvErrors.name: juniL2tpSessionStatPayRecvErrors
juniL2tpSessionStatPayRecvErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring reception errors.

juniL2tpSessionStatPayRecvDiscards.name: juniL2tpSessionStatPayRecvDiscards
juniL2tpSessionStatPayRecvDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded after reception.

juniL2tpSessionStatPaySendErrors.name: juniL2tpSessionStatPaySendErrors
juniL2tpSessionStatPaySendErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring transmission errors.

juniL2tpSessionStatPaySendDiscards.name: juniL2tpSessionStatPaySendDiscards
juniL2tpSessionStatPaySendDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded before transmission.

juniL2tpSessionStatRecvOutOfSequence.name: juniL2tpSessionStatRecvOutOfSequence
juniL2tpSessionStatRecvOutOfSequence.description: The number of packets received out of sequence.

juniL2tpSessionStatResequencingTimeouts.name: juniL2tpSessionStatResequencingTimeouts
juniL2tpSessionStatResequencingTimeouts.description: The number of reassembly timeouts that have occurred.

juniL2tpSessionStatPayLostPackets.name: juniL2tpSessionStatPayLostPackets
juniL2tpSessionStatPayLostPackets.description: When sequence numbers are enabled, this value represents the estimated number of payload packets lost, based on observed gaps in sequence numbers. This estimate is subject to correction (decrement) upon receipt of out-of-sequence packets that fill previously observed gaps.

juniL2tpUdpIpDestTable.name: juniL2tpUdpIpDestTable
juniL2tpUdpIpDestTable.description: The L2TP UDP/IP destination table. Reports the UDP/IP characteristics of a L2TP UDP/IP destination. A L2TP UDP/IP destination is associated with a local router, a local IP address, and with a remote IP address for the L2TP peer. More specific UDP/IP detail per tunnel is reported in the juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelTable.

juniL2tpUdpIpDestEntry.name: juniL2tpUdpIpDestEntry
juniL2tpUdpIpDestEntry.description: Describes the UDP/IP attributes of an L2TP destination.

juniL2tpUdpIpDestIfIndex.name: juniL2tpUdpIpDestIfIndex
juniL2tpUdpIpDestIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

juniL2tpUdpIpDestRouterIndex.name: juniL2tpUdpIpDestRouterIndex
juniL2tpUdpIpDestRouterIndex.description: The index of an entry in the juniRouterTable for the local router with which this L2TP destination interface is associated.

juniL2tpUdpIpDestLocalAddress.name: juniL2tpUdpIpDestLocalAddress
juniL2tpUdpIpDestLocalAddress.description: This L2TP destination's local IP address.

juniL2tpUdpIpDestRemoteAddress.name: juniL2tpUdpIpDestRemoteAddress
juniL2tpUdpIpDestRemoteAddress.description: The IP address of the remote L2TP endpoint.

juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelTable.name: juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelTable
juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelTable.description: The L2TP UDP/IP tunnel table. Reports the UDP/IP characteristics of L2TP UDP/IP tunnels. A L2TP UDP/IP tunnel is defined in terms of the local and remote IP addresses and UDP ports.

juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelIfIndex.name: juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelIfIndex
juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelIfIndex.description: Same as the value of ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRouterIndex.name: juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRouterIndex
juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRouterIndex.description: The index of an entry in the juniRouterTable for the local router with which this L2TP tunnel interface is associated.

juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelLocalAddress.name: juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelLocalAddress
juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelLocalAddress.description: The local IP address for this UDP/IP tunnel.

juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelLocalPort.name: juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelLocalPort
juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelLocalPort.description: The local UDP port for this UDP/IP tunnel.

juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteAddress.name: juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteAddress
juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteAddress.description: The remote IP address for this UDP/IP tunnel.

juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemotePort.name: juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemotePort
juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemotePort.description: The remote UDP port for this UDP/IP tunnel.

juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteReceiveAddress.name: juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteReceiveAddress
juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteReceiveAddress.description: The remote receive IP address for this UDP/IP tunnel. This object will differ from juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteAddress when the tunnel uses separate transmit and receive addresses to the remote peer.

juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteReceivePort.name: juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteReceivePort
juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemoteReceivePort.description: The remote receive UDP port for this UDP/IP tunnel. This object will differ from juniL2tpUdpIpTunnelRemotePort when the tunnel uses separate transmit and receive ports to the remote peer.
